'''Gordon Hutton Bremner''' (born 12 November 1917) was a Scottish professional [[association football|footballer]] who played for [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]], as an [[inside forward]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arsenal.com/history/profiles/76/gordon-bremner |title=Gordon Bremner |work=www.arsenal.com |publisher=Arsenal FC |accessdate=27 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player11/gordonbremner.htm |title=Gordon Bremner |accessdate=26 August 2015|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> He also played in wartime matches for [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] and the [[Scottish League XI]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.londonhearts.com/SFL/players/gordonbremner.html |title=Gordon Bremner |work= |publisher=London Hearts Supporters' Club |accessdate=27 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scotlandunoff/players/gordonhuttonbremner.html |title=Gordon Hutton Bremner |work= |publisher=London Hearts Supporters' Club |accessdate=27 May 2014}}</ref>

